  "target_response": {
    "text": "Resting heart rate is how many times your heart beats per minute when you're fully at rest, usually captured overnight, and it's one of the simplest fitness and recovery signals: lower and stable generally means your body is coping well. Yours looks good. Today's 57 bpm sits right at your 30-day average of 58.6 bpm, and your 7-day average is also 57 bpm, so nothing is drifting. The useful way to read it is against your own baseline rather than any chart: a jump of several beats above your usual for a couple of mornings often means fatigue, poor sleep, or oncoming illness. Your setup doesn't compute a recovery score, so keep an eye on this number and your HRV together as your day-to-day check.",
